\section{Limitations}
\paragraph{Retrieval evaluation.} Path-pattern relevance is a \emph{proxy}; upgrading to stable chunk IDs improves precision when ingestion is frozen. Lexical groundedness only detects the \emph{presence} of required tokens, not their correct use. Metrics transfer only to the corpus version and embedding checkpoint reported alongside the JSON artifact.

\paragraph{Case study.} Validation AMS is \emph{not} the private leaderboard score~\cite{adam2015higgs}; we use it to anchor reproducibility, not to claim competitive ranking. A single train/validation split with one random seed bounds the confidence one should place on point estimates.

\section{Reproducibility}\label{sec:repro}

\paragraph{Build the index (one-off).}
\begin{verbatim}
rag-ai-scientist setup-rag \
  --project-root ~/Desktop/higgs \
  --collection-name higgs-rag --force
\end{verbatim}
This uses \texttt{configs/references.yaml}, which points at \texttt{references/}, \texttt{docs/}, and top-level \texttt{README.md}, so ATLAS, CMS, and methodology documents all enter the collection.

\paragraph{Run the pipeline.}
\begin{verbatim}
python run_neurips_pipeline.py \
  --rag-db ~/Desktop/higgs/.cursor/rag_db \
  --collection higgs-rag
\end{verbatim}
(or split eval and paper rendering across environments via \texttt{--reuse-eval-json}).

\paragraph{Future work: code-quality evaluation.}
